{
  "stem": "2718.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I think that that was a time when I was really-- I was really convinced that this must be-- these people must be the scum of the earth.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because people who-- who lived, who worked for us, people who-- who were-- were on-- really on every day terms, and I'm not singling out anybody.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But they were lining the streets but by the hundreds, by the thousands, they were spitting at us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were throwing stones at us-- old people, little children walking with their-- with their parents, on-- on arm, and toddlers.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I mean, just the feeling was indescribable.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was-- there was never a matter of fear.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were not afraid.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We were not afraid because we were past the stage of being afraid.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And, of course, we had the Hungarian gendarmes very happily carrying the-- performing their task.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "In the ghetto, we had-- just to go back again to the ghetto, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the ghetto was used for interrogations.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they used-- they didn't make any excuses for interrogations, nor-- nor did they try to do it in a discreet way.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Because they picked-- they picked one-- one building in the ghetto, which was in the middle of it, one house.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They kicked out the people who were living there at that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And when they interrogated people, those people, I think, they had a very hard time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the interrogations-- [INAUDIBLE] those interrogations, at that time, were mostly to-- to discover where people have hidden their-- their personal fortunes.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some people did, some people didn't.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What people-- what they call fortunes, it was-- I don't know what they called fortunes, but they were after everything-- everything that-- and anything, what they could-- what they could get.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
